# Architecture

## Folder responsibilities

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `app/` | Routes, layouts, server actions entry points |
| `components/` | UI only — no business rules |
| `lib/domain/` | Business logic, services, domain types |
| `lib/db/` | Supabase client, repositories, typed queries |
| `lib/integrations/` | Provider adapters (WhatsApp, Instagram, Chatwoot, etc.) |
| `lib/security/` | Auth helpers, validation, permissions, audit |
| `supabase/migrations/` | Schema migrations |

## Layer flow

```txt
UI → Server Actions / API Routes → Domain Services → Repositories → Provider Adapters
```

## Rules

- Do **not** place business logic directly in UI components; extract to `lib/domain/` or hooks that call domain services
- Do **not** couple CRM domain models to WhatsApp/Instagram/Meta/Twilio payloads
- Provider-specific code stays in `lib/integrations/` behind `ChannelProvider` interface
- Domain services must not import provider SDKs

Reference: `docs/03-architecture.md`, `docs/05-integration-strategy.md`
